"It s been a bumper holiday season for the owners of rental homes on the Riviera of Cape Town the ribbon of prime coastal property that stretches from the V&amp;A Waterfront on the north shore of Table Mountain all the way down the west side of the Cape Peninsula to Hout Bay " said Charl and Ad l Louw principals of the Chas Everitt International franchise on the Atlantic Seaboard. "Daily rentals of R5,000 to R6,000 for a two-to three-bedroom apartment in Bantry Bay or Clifton were easily obtained while a spacious eight-bedroom multilevel villa with every mod con and panoramic views we have on our books achieves as much as R150,000 a day in season " they said. This story was originally published on BusinessLIVE. Read the full story here.- TMG Digital/BusinessLive